time required: 30 minutes
---

½ cup Jasmine Rice
2 unit Mini Cucumber
2 unit Scallions
4 ounce Shredded Carrots
1.5 ounce Sesame Dressing
5 teaspoon White Wine Vinegar
10 ounce Steelhead Trout
1 unit Japanese Yuzu Miso Glaze
Salt
Pepper
¼ teaspoon Sugar

• Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.
• In a small pot, combine rice, ¾ cup water (1 ½ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, 15-18 minutes.
• Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

• Wash and dry produce. Quarter cucumbers lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick quarter-moons. Trim and thinly slice scallions, separating whites from greens.
• Add cucumbers, scallion whites, carrots, dressing, 1 tsp vinegar (2 tsp for 4 servings), and ¼ tsp sugar (½ tsp for 4) to a medium bowl; stir to combine. (Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more.) Season generously with salt and pepper.

• Pat trout* dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper.
• Place trout, skin sides down, on a baking sheet. Evenly spread tops of trout with Omsom Japanese Yuzu Miso Glaze. Roast on top rack until trout is cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

• Fluff rice with a fork.
• Divide rice, trout, and cucumber carrot salad between plates. Sprinkle everything with scallion greens and serve.

***Trout is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.***